values:
I love my roommate. Really I do. But he is the most picky and finicky person in the world. I&nbsp;am trying to plan his birthday party and&nbsp;all he keeps telling me is that no one except me cares about him.&nbsp;Granted he&nbsp;has depression but sometimes&nbsp;I think he just&nbsp;makes himself depressed.&nbsp; Anyway, I am planning his birthday party and here is my dilemma. He does not like people looking at him so karaoke is out.Our neighbor&nbsp;will put in a noise complaint if there are people over.&nbsp; He does not like the sun, so outdoor activity is out. Paintball is very far from us.&nbsp;There is no laser tag in the area. Go Karting is very far and very expensive.&nbsp;So I&nbsp;finally figured out&nbsp;"Hey everyone&nbsp;likes bowling right?" I put down the sizable non refundable deposit. I harrassed the place into giving me exactly what i wanted. I hounded the food place to give me a 30 % discount. I wrangled up friends he hasnt seen in years.&nbsp;

Then:
An acquaintance of&nbsp;ours tells us that he went bowling&nbsp;for a work sponsored bonding type thing and I (a little tipsy) lean over and whisper&nbsp;what i am doing for&nbsp;roommate). Roommate figures it out of course and then tells acquaintance "I hate bowling".

Okay. he figured it out and then said "I hate&nbsp;bowling" loud enough for me to hear. Then he follows me into the bar and said why did you think bowling would be a good idea. And i am pissed off. He is always complaining that no one cares but that&nbsp;is all we can&nbsp;figure out with the limitations. He wont stray far from our neighborhood because he is afraid of getting harassed,&nbsp;so we cant just take him to a different bar or club that we dont frequent. There is literally nothing else to do.&nbsp;There were massive amounts of email just to figure out something. But he maintains that all he wants for his birthday is to be surprised but that is bullshit. I think i am not going to do anything. I am really pissed off. I told him i was mad and he just dismissed my feelings.&nbsp;

Am I being self centered? it is his birthday but when someone does something nice for you and you dont like it arent you supposed to fake it?


I am open to suggestions if anyone has one.&nbsp;&nbsp;
